title: Transcript of media session by SHWF on Dr William Ho
content_text:
p>Following is the transcript (English portion) of a media session by the 
Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, on Dr William Ho's 
intention not to renew his contract as Chief Executive of the Hospital Authority 
before attending a dinner hosted by the Chinese Manufacturers' Association of 
Hong Kong tonight (June 23):  Reporter: Dr Chow, can you tell us your feeling towards Dr Ho's refusal to renew 
the contract?  Dr Chow: I feel both surprised and regret. I also know that he was under very

great pressure because he was also struck down by SARS (Severe Acute Respiratory 
Syndrome) during the epidemic. Knowing that he will be putting up a lot of 
pressure, so his decision, I understand, must have gone through a great deal of 
struggle before he made that decision. In fact, I have talked to the Chairman of 
the Hospital Authority, Mr Anthony Wu, after that was being made in the Hospital 
Authority board today. I promise him that I will try to work together with the

Authority board today. I promise him that I will try to work together with the 
Hospital Authority to arrange a transition and also try to find a most suitable 
person to replace him.  Reporter: Is it difficult for you to find a replacement?  Dr Chow: It is up to the Hospital Authority through a global search to find the 
right replacement. Of course, at the moment, we do not have a specific candidate 
for this position. But I am sure, with time we are able to find a suitable

for this position. But I am sure, with time we are able to find a suitable 
person.  Reporter: Would you find it within the Hospital Authority?  Dr Chow: I hope that the search will not just be confined to the Hospital 
Authority, but rather to Hong Kong as well as the overseas.
